deck: Fantomelle is a mysterious thief and survivor of the Paradise project
description:
Origin

Fantomelle is a young girl whom was experimented on by the Weapon X Program. Besides this, she is a master thief. Not much is known about her at this point except for the fact that she has a telepathic link with her pet-fox Culpepper.

Other Media

Games

X-men: Battle of the Atom

Fantomelle is featured in the mobile card game "X-Men: Battle of the Atom" based on the comic book story with the same name. Her cards are:

  • [Weapon X Renegades] Fantomelle
name: Fantomelle

deck: Mysterious Superpowered Assassin whose specialty is high-risk jobs, and hard-to-kill targets. Made this abundantly clear when he attempted to assassinate the United States President during a trip to China. Seems to know who Captain China really is.
description:
Enigmatic super-powered assassin and mercenary whose carved a path of chaos through the world for the last ten years. The bigger the target, the higher the risk, the better. He leaves a bloody cross as his calling card.

First run-in with Captain China happens when the villain targets a visiting President Obama, using the opportunity to draw the hero out. Despite his insistence on using high-powered/high-tech weaponry, is more than capable of going toe-to-toe with the superhero. Knows Captain China's real name, hinting at a possible connection or prior history between the two.

Trying to find out how Cross knows him becomes the Captain's own personal quest.
